other_tests.findings: Patient is alert and oriented times three. No scleral icterus, oropharynx clear. Heart sounds are regular. Lungs are clear to auscultation bilaterally. Abdomen is soft, non-distended, focally tender in the right lower quadrant with positive Rovsing's sign and no rebound tenderness. Well-healed surgical scar noted. Extremities have no edema and are warm with palpable dorsalis pedis pulses bilaterally.
